name: WWE Superstars
overview: WWE Superstars is a professional wrestling television program produced by WWE that originally aired on WGN America in the United States. It debuted on April 16, 2009 and ended its domestic broadcasting on April 7, 2011. After the final domestic TV broadcast the show moved to an internet broadcast format while maintaining a traditional television broadcast in international markets. The show features mid-to-low card WWE superstars and divas, in a format similar to the former show WWE Heat which served the same purpose. Big names such as John Cena and Randy Orton previously appeared on the show at its beginning. The show also previously featured talent from the now-defunct ECW brand.

episodes.name: Superstars #299: January 1, 2015
episodes.overview: This week on the first WWE Superstars of 2015, the new and improved Fandango arrives to clash in a battle of the dance against R-Truth. Also, Big Red Rowan returns as he looks to start his New Year right against the technically gifted Tyson Kidd. Plus, we recap a Raw that totally reeked of awesomeness.

episodes.name: Superstars #300: January 8, 2015
episodes.overview: On the 300th episode of WWE Superstars, Los Matadores battle the unorthodox Gold & Stardust. Jack Swagger looks for retribution against Titus O'Neil. Plus, we recap the first Raw of 2015 featuring the return of The Authority, which had severe consequences for several WWE Superstars.

episodes.name: Superstars #351: January 1, 2016
episodes.overview: This week, the dominant pairing of Jack Swagger and the World’s Strongest Man Mark Henry take on The Ascension in our marquee matchup. Also, Darren Young looks to kick of 2016 with a victory against the founder of the Rose Bush, Adam Rose. We also take a look back at the return of John Cena to Raw this past Monday.
